# Root-tiering allowlist — gate-sdk/SPEC.md §check-root-tiering. One tracked
# top-level entry per line (`#` comments and blanks ignored); a line may be a
# glob. Every tracked entry at the repo root must be covered here — a new root
# surface is a deliberate edit to this file, not a reflex scratch drop.

# Orientation files
README.md
LICENSE
CLAUDE.md
CONTRIBUTING.md
RELEASING.md
TASK-QUEUE.md
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# In-flight spec amendments (canon-kit lifecycle — transient root surface)
SPEC-*.md

# Workflow + gates machinery
.claude
.github
.workflow
scripts

# Shared assets
assets

# Public docs site (GitHub Pages serves this directory as the site root)
docs

# Runnable adoption walkthrough (registered as the evidence-kit demo suite)
demo

# Name-reservation placeholders (not developed in)
reserve

# The kits (this is a kit monorepo — each kit is a top-level root)
gate-sdk
lifecycle-kit
queue-kit
canon-kit
guard-kit
delegation-kit
context-kit
drift-kit
evidence-kit
site-kit
doctrine-kit
